    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I've heard some people say that focusing on these \"existential\" scenarios is actually dangerous because it gives governments an excuse to over-regulate and kill off innovation, which might be more important for solving real problems. Do you think that's a valid critique, or is that just an excuse to avoid taking safety seriously?",
